CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 4, 1943, pg. 14, reads: "Elkdom on Parade! ... Thousands See Colorful Event ... Nation Represented. Tuesday afternoon, the Elks held their famous annual convention parade.  Up and down the hills of Pittsburgh marched the members of the Antlered Herd to the cheers and applause of thousands of spectators.  While not as long as parades in other years, it was still colorful and entertaining... Maggie Hiawatha, a member of the Atlantic City police force for 19 years, and one of the participants in parade... - Courier Photos by Harris, Sockwell and Olmstead."
TitMainTitle: Annual Elks parade, with Atlantic City police force member Maggie Hiawatha standing in street with band in background, in front of Northside Elks Lodge No. 124, Wylie Avenue, Hill District
